<subSubSection id="C31D65119E0DC705FF6F6BEB61B083E1" pageId="1" pageNumber="246" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BB8369A9E0DC705FF6F6BEB61B083E1" blockId="1.[151,1437,510,1581]" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">
<emphasis id="B973EA889E0DC705FF6F6BEB616682C0" bold="true" box="[199,322,690,716]" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Externally, the new species closely resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C074D199E0DC705FCC86BEA657D82C1" authority="Hu, Wang &amp; Han, 2015" authorityName="Hu, Wang &amp; Han" authorityYear="2015" box="[864,1369,690,717]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Nola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pinratanoides">
<emphasis id="B973EA889E0DC705FCC86BEA641882C1" box="[864,1084,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">Nola pinratanoides</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF964B6B9E0DC705FBED6BEA657D82C1" author="Hu, Y. Q. &amp; Wang, M. &amp; Han, H. L." box="[1093,1369,690,717]" pageId="1" pageNumber="246" pagination="483 - 487" refId="ref2607" refString="Hu, Y. Q., Wang, M. &amp; Han, H. L. (2015) Two new species and five new records of Nola Leach, [1815] (Lepidoptera, Nolidae, Nolinae) from China. Zootaxa, 3920 (3), 483 - 487. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3920.3.7" type="journal article" year="2015">Hu, Wang &amp; Han, 2015</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="133C2A1F9E0DC705FAC26BEA60E082FE" captionStart="FIGURES" captionStartId="3.[151,266,1817,1841]" captionTargetBox="[165,1424,222,1767]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1435,181,1793]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES. 1–12. Nola spp., male adult &amp; male genitalia. 1–3. Nola nayongensis sp. nov. 1. male adult (holotype); 2 &amp; 3. male genitalia (holotype). 4–6. N. pinratanoides (illustration by Hu et al., 2015, China, Yulong). 4. male adult; 5 &amp; 6. male genitalia. 7–9. N. quadriguttula. 7. male adult; 8 &amp; 9. male genitalia. 10–12. N. canioralis. 10. male adult; 11 &amp; 12. male genitalia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404854" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404854/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">Figs 4–6</figureCitation>
), but the main diagnostic differences are found as follows: ground color of the forewing of the new species is pale brown with the white patches along the costal margin and a punctiform postmedial line. The forewing of 
<taxonomicName id="4C074D199E0DC705FACE6BA261178335" authorityName="Hu, Wang &amp; Han" authorityYear="2015" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Nola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pinratanoides">
<emphasis id="B973EA889E0DC705FACE6BA261178335" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">Nola pinratanoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a brown ground color, the diffused grayish white pattern at costal margin and wing base with a filiform postmedial line. In male genitalia, the new species can be separated by the combination of the following characters: a distally divided valva, a basally wide ventral lobe of valva, a bigger and wider sacculus, an apically rounded saccus and a shorter spine on the aedeagus. The male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName id="4C074D199E0DC705FBA36AD264CD83A9" authorityName="Hu, Wang &amp; Han" authorityYear="2015" box="[1035,1257,907,933]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Nola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pinratanoides">
<emphasis id="B973EA889E0DC705FBA36AD264CD83A9" box="[1035,1257,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">Nola pinratanoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a medially divided valva, a basally narrower ventral lobe of valva, a smaller sacculus, an apically pointed saccus and a longer spine on the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31D65119E0DC705FF6F6AAF618685E9" pageId="1" pageNumber="246" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB8369A9E0DC705FF6F6AAF62DA841D" blockId="1.[151,1437,510,1581]" box="[199,766,1014,1041]" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">
<emphasis id="B973EA889E0DC705FF6F6AAF617D841C" bold="true" box="[199,345,1014,1040]" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">Description.</emphasis>
Adult (
<figureCitation id="133C2A1F9E0DC705FE056AAE61CB841D" box="[429,495,1015,1041]" captionStart="FIGURES" captionStartId="3.[151,266,1817,1841]" captionTargetBox="[165,1424,222,1767]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1435,181,1793]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES. 1–12. Nola spp., male adult &amp; male genitalia. 1–3. Nola nayongensis sp. nov. 1. male adult (holotype); 2 &amp; 3. male genitalia (holotype). 4–6. N. pinratanoides (illustration by Hu et al., 2015, China, Yulong). 4. male adult; 5 &amp; 6. male genitalia. 7–9. N. quadriguttula. 7. male adult; 8 &amp; 9. male genitalia. 10–12. N. canioralis. 10. male adult; 11 &amp; 12. male genitalia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404854" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404854/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Wingspan 
<quantity id="4CFF9B7F9E0DC705FDD66AAF62DE841D" box="[638,762,1014,1041]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.45" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.4" pageId="1" pageNumber="246" unit="mm" value="14.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="14.0">14–15 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB8369A9E0DC705FF6F6D42653A8439" blockId="1.[151,1437,510,1581]" box="[199,1310,1051,1077]" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">Head white; collar brown; antenna brown, white at the base, bipectinate in male; labial palpi white.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB8369A9E0DC705FF6F6D66631784E5" blockId="1.[151,1437,510,1581]" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">Thorax with blackish brown scales. Forewing ground color pale brown; costal margin with the white patches; vein Sc black at the base; basal line undistinguishable; antemedial line dark brown, arc-shaped; medial line undistinguishable; postmedial line consists of double lines, punctiform, wavy; subterminal line undistinguishable, but veins armed with dark and short lines; terminal line blackish brown; cilia pale blackish brown. Hind wing ground color pale grayish; discal spot pale black; cilia gray.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB8369A9E0DC705FF6F6DAA61A88501" blockId="1.[151,1437,510,1581]" box="[199,396,1267,1293]" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">Abdomen brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB8369A9E0DC705FF6F6C4E646E85CD" blockId="1.[151,1437,510,1581]" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">
<emphasis id="B973EA889E0DC705FF6F6C4E615E853C" bold="true" box="[199,378,1302,1329]" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="133C2A1F9E0DC705FE226C4E622D853D" box="[394,521,1303,1329]" captionStart="FIGURES" captionStartId="3.[151,266,1817,1841]" captionTargetBox="[165,1424,222,1767]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1435,181,1793]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES. 1–12. Nola spp., male adult &amp; male genitalia. 1–3. Nola nayongensis sp. nov. 1. male adult (holotype); 2 &amp; 3. male genitalia (holotype). 4–6. N. pinratanoides (illustration by Hu et al., 2015, China, Yulong). 4. male adult; 5 &amp; 6. male genitalia. 7–9. N. quadriguttula. 7. male adult; 8 &amp; 9. male genitalia. 10–12. N. canioralis. 10. male adult; 11 &amp; 12. male genitalia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404854" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404854/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">Figs 2 &amp; 3</figureCitation>
). Uncus not developed; tegumen of moderate size; valva divided distally; dorsal lobe of valva rounded apically, longer than ventral lobe of valva, costal margin sclerotized slightly; ventral valva relatively short, a small spine located at apex of valva, ventral margin sclerotized; harpe slender, incurved, tapering and pointed apically; sacculus elliptic, almost as long as the ventral lobe of valva; saccus V-shaped, rounded apically. Aedeagus cylindrical, with a short and curved spine apically; vesica without cornuti.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB8369A9E0DC705FF6F6C92618685E9" blockId="1.[151,1437,510,1581]" box="[199,418,1483,1509]" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">
<emphasis id="B973EA889E0DC705FF6F6C92610185E9" bold="true" box="[199,293,1483,1509]" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
